_source.text: 319 Because Philammon was not so powerful as Glaucus of Carystus [129] and some other athletes of former times, he did not leave Olympia uncrowned: but because he fought better than all who entered against him, he was crowned and proclaimed victor.

text: 319 Because **Philammon** was not so powerful as Glaucus of **Carystus** [129] and some other athletes of
former times, he did not leave Olympia uncrowned: but because he fought **better** **than** all who entered against him, he was crowned and proclaimed victor.
